{
  "texts": [
    "To understand phenotypic differences in MBC tumor states, we projected TAAs onto the inferred joint space from integration of all samples (Methods) and applied diffusion map analysis.",
    "This revealed tumor state transition trajectory from a TNBC-enriched state to an MBC-specific state correlated with tumor growth regulation and reduced glycolytic processes (Fig. 4c, d).",
    "MBC-specific states were associated with inflammatory response, hypoxia, EMT and tumor necrosis.",
    "The expression of EMTand hypoxia-related genes, along with sample distribution on this trajectory confirmed their enrichment in MBC intratumoral hubs (Fig. 4e, f).",
    "Oncogenic pathways like PI3K-AKT, anti-inflammatory and glucose-deprivation pathways were enriched in MBC intratumoral hubs, while G2/M and pro-inflammatory pathways were downregulated (Supplementary Fig. 13e), suggesting an immunosuppressive environment in MBC intratumoral regions."
  ]
}